As a guy is not my place. I say its not my favourite movement but I respect your decision and you as a person and actually think its how you really are. Your not crazy for going through the change to me personally because you didn't change yourself due to what's popular now or because all the celebrities are doing it. Its actually because you actually felt like you were a girl, and did the transition at a time where it wasn't even accepted to just be gay. By saying its not my favourite movement I'm not bashing the LGBT(I DUNNO THE REST) community. I just don't agree with everything they say, or that they fight for.
None the less, I think I just had to come here and actually say that I admire the decision you made. I'm not against it if its genuinely coming from the inside.
